snippet.description:

BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED

 CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE AUSTIN/SAN ANTONIO TX 803 PM CDT SAT MAY 16 2020 THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY. THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT NETWORK THE ATASCOSA COUNTY SHERIFFS OFFICE IS SEARCHING FOR EDGAR NATHANIEL JESUS COLLINS, WHITE, MALE, 14 MONTHS OLD, BORN FEBRUARY 20, 2019, UNKNOWN HEIGHT, UKNOWN WEIGHT, BLACK HAIR, BR
OWN EYES, AND UNKNOWN DESCRIPTION OF CLOTHING. POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR CATHERINE ANGELINE OCON, WHITE, FEMALE, 28 YEARS OLD, BORN JANUARY 21, 1992, HEIGHT 5 FEET 4 INCHES, WEIGHT 120 POUNDS, BLACK HAIR, BROWN EYES, AND UNKNOWN DESCRIPTION OF CLOTHING, IN CONNECTION WITH EDGAR NATHANIEL JESUS COLLINS ABDUCTION. THE SUSPECT IS DRIVING A BLUE, 1999, PLYMOUTH, VOYAGER VAN WITH A TEXAS LICENSE PLATE NUMBER OF L...S...J...8...3...8...0. THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN POTEET, TX. LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR IMMEDIATE DANGER. IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE ATASCOSA COUNTY SHERIFFS OFFICE. NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS ATASCOSA COUNTY SHERIFFS OFFICE AT 8...3...0...7...6...9...3...4...3...4. END OF MESSAGE. $$
